# clawdputer / retro app — ROM source manifests
#
# Copy this file to your SD card as /roms/sources.txt to override the
# firmware's compiled-in default. Each non-comment line is a manifest URL.
#
# A manifest URL is either:
#   - A plain-text file — one ROM URL per line, optionally prefixed with
#     "Display name | " to override the shown name. '#' starts a line
#     comment.
#   - An HTML page — the downloader scrapes <a href> values pointing at
#     supported ROM extensions (.gb, .gbc, plus future cores).
#
# Optional "Display | URL" syntax works in this file too.

# --- The compiled-in default (kept here for reference) ---
Default manifest | https://chaerem.github.io/clawdputer/roms-manifest.txt

# --- Add your own manifests below ---
# A gist, your own server, or any HTML index page works. Example:
# My library | https://gist.githubusercontent.com/USER/HASH/raw/manifest.txt

# --- Sample manifest contents (one URL per line) ---
# https://example.com/roms/tetris.gb
# Pokemon Red | https://example.com/roms/pokemon_red.gbc
